.TH manta-cli-apply 1  "apply " 
.SH NAME
manta\-cli\-apply \- Apply changes to the system
.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBmanta\-cli apply\fR [\fB\-h\fR|\fB\-\-help\fR] [\fIsubcommands\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
Apply changes to the system
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-h\fR, \fB\-\-help\fR
Print help
.SH SUBCOMMANDS
.TP
manta\-cli\-apply\-hardware(1)
[experimental] Rescale a cluster\*(Aqs hardware allocation
.TP
manta\-cli\-apply\-configuration(1)
Create a configuration (deprecated — use \*(Aqapply sat\-file\*(Aq)
.TP
manta\-cli\-apply\-sat\-file(1)
Process a SAT file to create configurations, images, and session templates
.TP
manta\-cli\-apply\-boot(1)
Update boot parameters and runtime configuration
.TP
manta\-cli\-apply\-kernel\-parameters(1)
Replace kernel parameters on nodes
.TP
manta\-cli\-apply\-session(1)
Create and run a configuration session from a local repo
.TP
manta\-cli\-apply\-ephemeral\-environment(1)
Launch an ephemeral SSH environment from an image
.TP
manta\-cli\-apply\-template(1)
Boot nodes using an existing session template
